				<pubDate>Wed, 28 Mar 2018 21:39:14 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Captain Kirby</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3440103</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Wow. I'm just&#8230; +300 in a month? You guys are the best! So as a little thank you, I drafted up a small after-credits, non-canon thing.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">MTF&nbsp;Eta-10&nbsp;has&nbsp;been&nbsp;deployed.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Operation&nbsp;tentative&nbsp;success.&nbsp;Awaiting&nbsp;confirmation.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>SCP-3393 read the last line of its file, and then smiled to itself. It didn't need to look around to know that it'd been locked in. It sighed. And then the power was pulled from the computer.</p> <p><em>I mean, what could I expect? It's literally what they do for a living.</em></p> <p>It took some time to find some paper and a pen, but eventually it got around to writing. Took about thirty minutes to finish the draft. Luckily, this wasn't a formal containment cell, so there was a window in the door. SCP-3393 stuck the pages to the window, with the writing facing out.</p> <p>An hour later, Researcher Telby, in charge of SCP-3393, came by to inspect the cell. She noticed the papers stuck to the door window, since her mnestics were still effective. Telby transcribed them herself, and then reported it to the Site director.<br /> <br /> Three days later, Dr. Mackey's spouse received a will in the mail.</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> </div> <p>Thanks again! I'm happy you all enjoyed this!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
