				<wikidot:authorName>Captain Kirby</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3440103</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thanks! I'm glad you enjoyed it.</p> <blockquote> <p>Did you decide against the user module?</p> </blockquote> <p>So I tried it out, and showed it to a few people, but most of them felt like it was thumping the meta drum too hard. When you start out by telling the reader they're the anomaly, you're already walking a thin line between &quot;strong hook&quot; and &quot;loss of suspension of disbelief&quot;. The user module just tipped the balance too much in the direction of the latter.</p> 
				 	]]>
